  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN180.1-kilavi1"><app><lem>irantu</lem><rdg wit="#C5 #G1 #G2">om.</rdg></app> piṉṉiṉṟa talaimakaṟkuk kuṟainērnta tōḻi <app><lem>talaimakaḷaik</lem><rdg wit="#NL #C5 #C7 #G1 #G2">talaimakaṭkuk</rdg></app> kuṟainayappak kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante, who had granted the request of HIM who had stood behind [her] begging, said to HER so that she would agree to the request.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel"> 
          <p xml:id="AN180.1-kilavi2"><app><lem>talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉākat tōḻikkuc colliyatūumām.</lem><rdg wit="#NL #C5 #G1 #G2">missing</rdg></app></p> <!-- Is 'missing' the same as '/'? -->
          <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante said when HE was behind the hedge.</p>
        </div>

        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN180.1">
        <l>nakainaṉi yuṭaittāṟ ṟōḻi takaimikak</l>
        <l>kōtai yāyamoṭu kuvavumaṇa lēṟi</l>
        <l><supplied>vī</supplied>tatai kāṉal vaṇṭa layarak</l>
        <l>kataḻparit tiṇṭēr kaṭaii vantu</l>
        <l><supplied>ta</supplied>ṇkayat tamaṉṟa voṇpūṅ kuvaḷai</l>
        <l>yarumpalait tiyaṟṟiya curumpār kaṇṇi</l>
        <l>piṉṉup<supplied>puṟa</supplied>n tāḻak koḷaṉē cūṭṭi</l>
        <l>nalvara liḷamulai nōkki neṭituniṉaintu</l>
        <l>nillātu peyarntaṉa ṉoruva ṉataṟkē</l>
        <l>pulavunā ṟiruṅkaḻi tuḻaiip palavuṭaṉ</l>
        <l>pu<supplied>ḷ</supplied>ḷiṟai koṇṭa muḷḷuṭai neṭuntōṭṭut</l>
        <l>tāḻai maṇantu ñāḻaloṭu keḻīip</l>
        <l>paṭappai niṉṟa muṭa<supplied>ttā</supplied>ṭ puṉṉaip</l>
        <l>poṉṉēr nuṇṭātu nōkki</l>
        <l>yeṉṉu nōkkumiv vaḻuṅka lūrē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>It is full of laughter indeed, friend, (1a-c)</l>
        <l>– this noisy village that looks at me too, (15)</l>
        <l>looking at the gold-like fine pollen (14)</l>
        <l>of the Puṉṉai tree with a crooked trunk that stands in the garden, (13)</l>
        <l>joined with the Ñāḻal tree, united with the screwpine tree (12)</l>
        <l>with thorny long blades on which birds have taken [their] seat, (11)</l>
        <l>many together, after having stirred the fish-reeking dark backwaters. (10)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">Befittingly, (1d)</l>
        <l>when [I] mounted the heaped sand with [my] garlanded companions, (1)</l>
        <l>[and] was engaged in play in the seashore grove full of blossoms, (2)</l>
        <l>someone came, driving [his] firm chariot in hasty motion, (9c+4)</l>
        <l>adorned [me] – without taking [my permission!] – while [my] braids were hanging down [my] back, (7)</l>
        <l>with a chaplet full of bees, that had been made by moving the buds (6)</l>
        <l>of the bright-flowered blue waterlily thickly grown in the cool pond, (5)</l>
        <l>looked at [my] young breasts that are coming out well, thought long (8)</l>
        <l>[and] moved back without staying – therefore. (9)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
